    </refmeta>
    <refnamediv>
        <refname>&daps_init;</refname>
        <refpurpose> A command to set up a daps documentation directory</refpurpose>
    </refnamediv>
    <refsynopsisdiv id="daps_init.synopsis">
        <title>Synopsis</title>
        <cmdsynopsis>
      <command>&daps_init;</command>
      <arg choice="req">-d
        <replaceable>PATH_TO_DOC_DIR</replaceable></arg>
      <arg choice="opt">-r <replaceable>ROOT ELEMENT</replaceable></arg>
    </cmdsynopsis>
    </refsynopsisdiv>
    <refsect1>
        <title>Description</title>
        <para>&daps_init; is used in daps to create a new documentation project from scratch. It
            automatically sets up the key files and directory structure needed and creates an example document which can be used to explore dapsÂ´ functionality</para>
    </refsect1>
    <refsect1>
        <title>Options</title>
        <para>View the available Options with <command>&daps_init;</command></para>
        <para> Set the root element of your example dokument. Currently supported are "book"
            (default) and "article"</para>
        <cmdsynopsis>
            <command>&daps_init;</command>
            <arg choice="req">-r (article|book)</arg>
        </cmdsynopsis>
    </refsect1>

